Subject: Preparing to AES+GCM scratch optimization (reducing read operations
         by replacing in line with using  macro in loop)
From: Alexander Troosh <trush@yandex.ru>

Test of raw speed of GCM and CTR modes on e8v7 proto:

for m in  aes-128-gcm aes-256-gcm aes-192-gcm \
          aes-128-ctr aes-256-ctr aes-192-ctr
do
  openssl speed -evp $m 2>/dev/null | tail -1
done

aes-128-gcm        717.02k     1847.55k     4883.11k     8400.90k    10169.00k    10240.00k
aes-256-gcm        703.57k     1700.89k     4416.51k     7350.27k     8751.79k     8825.51k
aes-192-gcm        690.93k     1769.88k     4649.64k     8036.99k     9357.99k     9431.72k
aes-128-ctr        812.06k     2407.15k     7579.31k    16278.53k    24502.27k    25411.58k
aes-256-ctr        754.27k     2143.96k     6423.22k    12725.59k    17760.26k    18317.31k
aes-192-ctr        773.46k     2274.37k     6966.53k    14695.46k    20449.96k    21244.59k


